   - Internally, this calls `reader.deserialise(data)` which creates a `stream_read_adaptor`
   - The `stream_read_adaptor` then calls `data.serialise(adaptor)` which deserializes both `user_id` and `name`

Both implementations leverage the built-in functionality of the Hexi library to handle the serialization/deserialization process automatically by calling the object's `serialise` method with the appropriate stream adaptor.

